SANTA BARBARA , Calif ., Aug . 24 , 2011 -- / PRNewswire / -- The largest earthquake to hit Virginia in more than a century struck Louisa County yesterday . The 5 . 9 earthquake hit Virginia at 1 : 51 p . m . on August 23 , but the effects were felt in several states including Washington , New York City and North Carolina . No injuries or major damage were reported but many buildings were evacuated and masses of people flooded the streets .